---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About">
  <div class="container prose about">
    <h1>About the QSC Atlas</h1>
    <p>
      The QSC Atlas shows, country by country, how governments are migrating to quantum-safe
      cryptography: which post-quantum standards dominate, which international standards processes
      a country takes part in, and where one exists, its migration timeline.
    </p>
    <p>
      It draws on institutional sources only: government bodies, national agencies, and standards
      organisations. Each country profile links to the primary documents it is built from, so you
      can read the source for yourself. The Atlas is rebuilt as new institutional documents appear,
      so it reflects the current public record rather than a one-off snapshot.
    </p>

    <h2 id="briefing">Request a briefing</h2>
    <p>
      The Atlas is maintained alongside a consulting practice on the quantum-safe transition. If you
      would like a briefing tailored to your organisation or sector, get in touch.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a class="briefing-link" href="mailto:hello@example.com?subject=QSC%20Atlas%20briefing">
        Request a briefing
      </a>
    </p>
    <p class="note">Replace the contact address above with your real one before launch.</p>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .about h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-reading);
  }
  .about h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-reading);
    margin-top: var(--space-12);
  }
  .briefing-link {
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: var(--space-2) var(--space-4);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: var(--font-instrument);
  }
  .note {
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
</style>
